theorem
Th5: (for X holds (((the addF of X) is  commutative  associative & (the addF of X) is  having_a_unity) implies (for S being  finite (Subset of X) holds (S is non empty implies (for L being (linear-Functional of X) holds ( L . ( setsum S ) ) = ( setopfunc (S,(the carrier of X),( REAL ),L,( addreal )) ))))))
proof
let X;
assume that
A1: ((the addF of X) is  commutative  associative & (the addF of X) is  having_a_unity);
let S being  finite (Subset of X);
assume S is non empty;
then A2: ( ( 0 ) + 1 ) <= ( card S ) by INT_1:7;
let L being (linear-Functional of X);
consider p being (FinSequence of (the carrier of X)) such that A3: (p is  one-to-one & ( rng p ) = S) and A4: ( setsum S ) = ( (the addF of X) "**" p ) by A1,CKB1:def 1;
reconsider q1 = ( Func_Seq (L,p) ) as (FinSequence of ( REAL ));
A5: (for i holds (i in ( dom p ) implies ( q1 . i ) = ( L . ( p . i ) )))
proof
let i;
assume that
A6: i in ( dom p );
( q1 . i ) = ( ( L * p ) . i ) by BHSP_5:def 4
.= ( L . ( p . i ) ) by A6,FUNCT_1:13;
hence thesis;
end;
A7: ( dom L ) = (the carrier of X) by FUNCT_2:def 1;
now
let xd being set;
A8: (xd in ( dom p ) implies ( p . xd ) in ( rng p )) by FUNCT_1:3;
(xd in ( dom ( Func_Seq (L,p) ) ) iff xd in ( dom ( L * p ) )) by BHSP_5:def 4;
hence (xd in ( dom ( Func_Seq (L,p) ) ) iff xd in ( dom p )) by A7,A8,FUNCT_1:11;
end;
then A9: ( dom ( Func_Seq (L,p) ) ) = ( dom p ) by TARSKI:1;
( len p ) >= 1 by A3,A2,FINSEQ_4:62;
then ( L . ( (the addF of X) "**" p ) ) = ( ( addreal ) "**" q1 ) by A9,A5,CKB11:1;
hence thesis by A7,A3,A4,BHSP_5:def 5;
end;
